    "what_description": "Ziziphus jujuba is a deciduous shrub or small tree native to Asia, belonging to the family Rhamnaceae. It grows up to 10 meters in height, with a broad, rounded crown and a short, straight trunk, typically 10-30 cm in diameter. The leaves are dark green, ovate, 2-5 cm in length, and have a serrated margin, with 2-3 pairs of secondary veins. The flowers are small, greenish-yellow, and grow in clusters in the axils of the leaves. The fruit is a small, red or yellow drupe, 1-2 cm in diameter, containing a single seed.",
